{"id":"d=origam-topic-4085//p=1a670eb4fd1547fba6ff94fff4eab152","tags":{"__document_id":["origam-topic-4085"],"__file_type":["text/plain"],"__file_id":["e44572b11ae74abf95317ba560c7f2ee"],"__file_part":["ab8019673dc34d5b9fe276b9756933ab"],"__part_n":["2"],"__sect_n":["0"],"source":["origam-community"],"category":["docs"],"categoryId":["8"],"topicId":["4085"],"url":["https://community.origam.com/t/how-to-create-sequential-workflows/4085"],"title":["How to create Sequential Workflows"]},"payload":{"url":"","schema":"20231218A","file":"content.txt","text":" not in the standard grid view of your entity. We will use the second solution here, create a  Task  screen copy named  TaskSelection  with selection boxes added. After that we also need to update the  Screen  setting in the workflow task properties and select our new screen there \u2013 in other words use our new screen in that workflow UI. \n   Step 3: Change task data \n In this step, the assignee of all selected tasks is changed to the current user. One of the Task fields is updated in the Context store for all tasks selected in the previous step. \n Create a new  (Task) Service Method Call  using the  DataTransformationService  and its  Transform  method: \n          Transformation service step  556\u00D7396 64.3 KB         \n Now set up the transformation script (XSLT) that will modify the data in the Context store. \n In the Model Browser, navigate to  Business Logic / Transformations  and create a new  XSL Transformation (XSLT)  under your package. \n The transformation looks as follows: \n  \u003C?xml version=\u00221.0\u0022 encoding=\u0022UTF-8\u0022?\u003E\n\u003Cxsl:stylesheet xmlns:xsl=\u0022http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform\u0022 version=\u00221.0\u0022\n\txmlns:AS=\u0022http://schema.advantages.cz/AsapFunctions\u0022\n\txmlns:date=\u0022http://exslt.org/dates-and-times\u0022 exclude-result-prefixes=\u0022AS date\u0022\u003E\n\n\t\u003Cxsl:template match=\u0022ROOT\u0022\u003E\n\t\t\u003CROOT\u003E\n\t\t\t\u003Cxsl:apply-templates select=\u0022Task[@Selected=\u0027true\u0027]\u0022/\u003E\n\t\t\u003C/ROOT\u003E\n\t\u003C/xsl:template\u003E\n\n\t\u003Cxsl:template match=\u0022Task\u0022\u003E\n\t\t\u003Cxsl:copy\u003E\n\t\t\t\u003Cxsl:copy-of select=\u0022@*\u0022/\u003E\n\t\t\t\u003Cxsl:attribute name=\u0022refAssignedToId\u0022\u003E\n\t\t\t\t\u003Cxsl:value-of select=\u0022AS:ActiveProfileId()\u0022/\u003E\n\t\t\t\u003C/xsl:attribute\u003E\n\t\t\t\u003Cxsl:copy-of select=\u0022*\u0022/\u003E\n\t\t\u003C/xsl:copy\u003E\n\t\u003C/xsl:template\u003E\n\u003C/xsl:stylesheet\u003E\n  \n For more details, see the  tutorial related to XSL transformations . This example corresponds to the second example described there. \n Finally, reference your transformation script in the workflow step parameters. Create a new  Transformation Reference  in the step and select your script: \n          Transformation reference in model  267\u00D7305 32.2 KB         \n The last part of this step is to add a  Context Store Reference  to the step\u2019s  Data  section with the source data: \n          Context store reference settings  343\u00D7263 26.4 KB         \n Note: Remember changing the  CastToDataType  property to  XML , as that is the data type you work with. \n   Step 4: Save changed tasks \n In this final step, all modified tasks are saved to the database. \n Create a new  (Task) Service Method Call , again using  DataService  and its  StoreData  method: \n          Store data workflow step  532\u00D7377 58.8 KB         \n Then connect this step to the previous one by setting up the dependency. \n Finally, add a new  Context Store Reference  to the  Data  section of this step, the same way as in the previous step. \n   Workflow overview \n Below is the complete workflow structure and content, shown both in the diagram editor and in the model browser: \n          Four-step workflow in editor  437\u00D7601 35.4 KB         \n          Complete workflow in model browser  315\u00D7727 77.3 KB         \n   Actions \n To create workflows more quickly, you can use some predefined actions over the context store: \n          Context store actions  542\u00D7322 25.4 KB         \n Here, you can either select individual steps for working with data \u2014 load, transform, and store \u2014 or an entire sequence comprising all these model steps. This will pre-generate a three-step workflow for you: \n          Generated 3-step workflow  447\u00D7542 33 KB         \n Then, for example, all you need to do is add your chosen transformation, and you\u2019re pretty much done. For workflows of this type, this action can save you a lot of clicking. \n   Fine-tuning your workflow \n   Workflow step labels \n To make the second step, where the user selects tasks, more user-friendly, change the workflow step label. ","vector_provider":"AI.Ollama.OllamaTextEmbeddingGenerator","vector_generator":"__","last_update":"2026-04-29T00:22:50"},"vector":[-0.049004894,-4.277197E-05,-0.05357078,0.002077571,-0.00828606,0.0037629392,0.012703063,-0.024510348,0.017638888,0.004793592,0.038639426,0.010467507,0.018111233,-0.018695353,0.046167973,0.011472987,-0.046968017,0.007102241,0.043880258,-0.014972231,-0.030884497,-0.024498375,0.010813493,0.024166936,-0.01492324,0.012143371,-0.021589044,-0.031151682,0.037848506,0.01830375,0.007969107,-0.054083057,0.024554085,-0.053626627,-0.011295387,0.01104313,-0.0065608667,-0.003601218,-0.0448759,0.014863969,-0.014182424,0.0113827055,0.008447829,0.00038158306,0.036109503,-0.0076439334,-0.023023842,-0.03701874,0.0049129664,-0.049378015,-0.05781822,-0.00046194496,-0.0008225346,-0.036780152,0.046263464,0.025717065,-0.0686689,-0.024336781,-0.073145054,0.010087957,-0.056478642,0.039394353,0.02099896,0.016746838,0.031069787,0.035677776,-0.019426936,0.018399928,-0.014221248,-0.022849547,0.013306227,0.023440663,-0.07043636,-0.007202735,-0.045808878,-0.018665463,-0.013858403,-0.008199256,0.036702335,0.026323175,-0.016146908,0.026654689,0.0060868473,